8:
I-I'm sorry we can't be of any more
help to you!
11:
Don't worry about it. Focus on
getting your friend the healing he
needs!
15:
There are so many of them... We
mustn't let even a single one
through, Alk!
19:
You there—the one still able to fight.
Buy me some time, won't you?
29:
Heed me, spirits of water... Unleash
an endless torrent before me!
35: There we go. That went well, I'd say.
39:
Thank you! You really helped us out
there.
43:
My pleasure. You did a pretty good
job yourself too.
46:
W-wait! Before you leave, at least
tell us your name!
49:
I'm not sure I did anything that
warrants announcing my name like
that, but... all right.
56: Man... That girl was pretty cool, huh?
60:
Indeed. She knew how to make a
memorable entrance and exit.
Perhaps she was actually a mage of
some renown—
77:
Were you assailed by a monster?
We'll get you treatment right away!
80:
Er, no, no. That's not it. I just... ran out
of steam from using all that magic
back there.
84:
Also, my magic tome is just super
heavy... But I can't exactly cast spells
without it, so I've got no choice but
to lug it around.
87:
Have you thought about perhaps
hiring a personal porter to carry it
for you?
90:
You mean have someone carry my
stuff for me? No way. I have a
reputation to keep up.
93:
I'd rather rough it on my own than
resort to doing something as
embarrassing as that.
96:
Though I guess napping on the floor
of the Kaleidoscope isn't exactly
"cool," huh.
100:
...And my massive book probably
isn't helping much in that
department either.
105:
Let us escort you to the entrance! It's
the least we can do, after you
helped us out back there.
108:
Did I, though? I feel like you would
have taken care of things just fine
even without me.
111:
I don't know about that... Having you
there was a really big help!
116: You're too nice, you know that?
118:
I guess I can't embarrass myself any
MORE today... I'll just have to take
you up on that offer.
123: Oh, we shouldn't go that way.
126:
I was fighting monsters over there
and used a bunch of water
magic—the whole place is covered
in mud. We'll get our clothes dirty.
129: That's... a deal-breaker for you, huh?
135:
Man... Adventuring really is a whole
lot easier when you're not alone.
138:
You helped us out too! That route
you showed us got us out of there
super fast.
143:
Agreed! And I must say, the magic
you employ strikes me as quite
different from that of other mages in
the area.
146:
Oh, yeah. That's 'cause I spent time
enhancing it using all the latest
advancements in magic research.
156:
To tell you the truth, running around
solo's gotten to be a bit of a chore
for me.
158:
If you guys would be willing to take
me along, I'd be super grateful.
161:
Plus, now that you've seen how
uncool I really am, I need to monitor
you carefully! Otherwise you might
go spreading some terrible rumors
about me.
166:
Of course you can join us.
We welcome you, Façon.
170:
Th-that was a way faster response
than I expected...
175:
Well, we're pretty confident we can
count on you!
178:
Really? Even though I was lying there
passed out on the floor of the
Kaleidoscope?
182:
Only because you spent all your
energy helping us and those other
adventurers out!
191:
Plus, if it would make you feel more
at ease, we've got secrets of our
own we can share with you!
198:
Those are all different worlds?! That
is so awesome!
202: It's to your liking, I take it?
206:
Yep! Turns out your secret was
pretty darn cool.
209:
This seems like a great place to
continue my research—both on
magic AND fashion!
